'''PP-19''' is a character from the Tactical SRPG ES game '''[[Girls' Frontline]]''' developed by MicaTeam and published by Digital Sky and its derivatives.

== Historical basis ==

A new model of submachine gun was developed in 1993 by two engineers of Izhmash, Viktor Kalashnikov and Alexey Dragunov, son of the designer of the AK and the SVD, respectively. The weapon is named ''Bizon'' (Bison).

The Bizon's receiver resembles that of the AK, and the weapon has 60% of its parts shared with the AK-100 family of assault rifle. The Bizon also borrowed the firing mechanism wholesale from the AK-74M, albeit using a simple blowback mechanism instead of a gas-operated bolt. The Bizon can accept different types of rear sights and stocks if needed, and evolved into the Bizon-2 and the Bizon-3.

